5:
The village isn't much farther. We
can finally have a draft to soothe
our throats.
16:
Marco... *hic* Marco won't let me
play with them... *sniff* He says it's
'cause they're dogs and I'm a cat...
19:
So at long last, the cat and dogfolk
have begun to live alongside one
another...
22:
But I see they have not yet learned
to love their neighbors.
26: Come on. It's just kids being kids.
29:
If... If I was stronger, they wouldn't be
able to hurt me no more...
32:
Hey, Nimbus. Why don't you teach
him some of your cool moves?
36: What? Why the hell would I do that?
40:
At the very least, it will be a way to
pass the time. We mean to lodge
here tonight.
45:
All right, fine... Hey, kid. What's your
name?
52:
If I hear one mewl outta you, I'm
sending you home. That clear, Neo?
56:
You've got guts, but your form's all
over the place...
61:
Hey... The hell are you doing here? If
you've got something to say, just
say it.
65:
I'd better not. If we give the kid
conflicting advice, it's only going to
confuse him.
69:
Talk. I don't need you there silently
judging me.
74:
...You're teaching the kid to street
fight.
83:
Do you really think that's what's best
for him? Street fighting is about
devastating your opponent as
quickly and brutally as possible.
85:
It's a sure way of making enemies
for life.
93:
Sorry. I didn't mean to waste your
time.
97:
Wait. You can't just say your piece
and leave.
101: You're the one who made me say it.
105:
I'm asking for your help, Mormia.
You've got something better to offer
Neo, right?
113:
Save your breath. I can see it written
all over your face.
122: Hey, kid. You don't suck anymore.
125:
Guess your advice worked. You use
to be an instructor or something?
128:
No, but... Watching him reminded
me of my past.
133: I heard you were from another world.
135:
...I don't remember much about my
birthplace.
141:
But there's one sensation from
childhood that haunts me even now.
142:
I was always alone. So I told myself I
needed to get stronger fast, to
protect myself.
147:
I was so desperate for power, I lost
sight of some important things. And
now I know better. That's all.
155: You here for a fight? Let's go then!
157: Why won't you let me be your friend?
162: Looks like you were right, Mormia.
167:
There is no surer way to victory than
befriending the enemy.
171:
It doesn't always work. But with
these kids, there was hope.
175:
Well, let's get going. We've got
nothing left to do here, right?
180:
Take me with you! I wanna grow up
to be strong like Nimbus and
Mormia!
188: Is this the kind of power you want?
192:
That wasn't true strength. That was
violence. And it creates more
problems than it solves. No one
should have to rely on itleast of all
you.
203:
And now you have friends. Wherever
they are... that's your place of
strength.
210:
Sorry we have to say goodbye so
soon. But I'm glad we met.
